# GreenOR — AI Context

## Project
GreenOR is a surgical sustainability platform. It lets surgical teams log instruments/supplies used per OR case, calculates carbon emissions, and surfaces insights through dashboards and gamification.

## Tech Stack
- Next.js 14 (App Router, TypeScript)
- Tailwind CSS with custom design system
- Supabase (PostgreSQL + auth via magic links + RLS)
- Vercel for hosting
- Resend for branded emails

## Design System
- Font: Palatino everywhere (never Inter, Arial, or system fonts)
- Background: warm beige #F9F5EE
- Primary: forest green #1B4332
- Cards: white bg, border 0.5px solid #E5E0D8, rounded-2xl
- Inputs: white bg, border #E5E0D8, rounded-xl, focus:border-green-500 focus:ring-2 focus:ring-green-50
- Primary buttons: bg-green-900 text-white font-bold rounded-xl hover:bg-green-700
- Secondary buttons: border-2 border-beige-300 bg-white rounded-xl hover:border-green-300
- Emissions colors: green-700 < 4kg, amber-700 4-8kg, red-700 > 8kg
- Every card gets hover-lift class, every button gets tap-scale class
- Animations defined in globals.css (fade-up, slide-right, slide-left, scale-in, etc.)

## Key Rules
1. Type `cookiesToSet` explicitly as `{ name: string; value: string; options?: any }[]` in supabase-server.ts and middleware.ts
2. Export viewport config in layout.tsx with maximumScale: 1 for iOS
3. All pages must work at 375px width
4. No horizontal overflow at any screen size
5. Use collapse-content/open CSS pattern for expandable sections
6. Emission formula: Σ(item qty × emission_factor_kg) + Σ(tray qty × per_use_emission_kg)
7. Auth is magic link only — no passwords
8. Duration, anesthesia type, and anesthesia gas are REQUIRED fields

## File Structure
- lib/supabase-browser.ts — browser client
- lib/supabase-server.ts — server client
- lib/types.ts — all TypeScript interfaces and constants
- lib/emissions.ts — emission calculation and formatting utilities
- middleware.ts — auth redirect for /dashboard/*
- app/dashboard/log/page.tsx — 7-step case logging wizard

## Database Tables
profiles, cpt_codes, equipment, instrument_sets, cases, case_items, case_sets
Views: cases_with_details, emissions_by_approach
